- "bustling hubs of travel" refers to cities with a high number of travel packages;
- "stand out as the most popular destinations" refers to cities with the highest number of packages;
- "average cost of these packages" is calculated by summing the costs of all packages in a city and dividing by the number of packages.

sql:
SELECT package_name, category, cost
FROM travel_packages
ORDER BY cost DESC;

SELECT package_name, days
FROM travel_packages
WHERE days = (SELECT MAX(days) FROM travel_packages);

SELECT MAX(total_revenue) AS max_revenue
FROM (
    SELECT package_id, SUM(total_cost) AS total_revenue
    FROM bookings
    GROUP BY package_id
) AS revenue_summary;

external_knowledge:
- "Most recently booked" refers to the latest booking date for each package;
- "Most recently reviewed" refers to the latest review date for each package;
- "Average booking cost" is the mean total cost of the most recent bookings for each package;
- "Average rating" is the mean of all ratings given to each package;
- "Top reviewer" is the user who wrote the most recent review for each package.

- "top 3 travel packages" refers to the packages with the highest average ratings;
- "crafted these magical journeys" refers to the travel agents who created the travel packages;
- "stellar performance" refers to the high average ratings given by users.

- 'shining stars' refers to the top-rated travel packages;
- 'categories' include types of travel packages such as honeymoon, romantic getaway, etc.;
- 'user reviews' are the ratings provided by customers who have booked and used the travel packages.

